<br />

<br />
They aren't there.  I have tried game after game and none of them offer the depth of gameplay that EQ does.  All of the games that are touted as &quot;next generation&quot; are only next generation in graphics.  Graphically EQ stinks, but as far as a gaming aspect it is still pretty much the Gold standard.
<br />

<br />
Asherons Call, Earth and Beyond, Star Wars Galaxies, Horizons, City of Heroes.  I played all of these games, and none of them offers the same game play depth that Everquest does.  All of them tried to change EQ standards in various ways.  Tired of Mana and Resting for Health, City of Heroes has all your skills on recharge timers.  Don't like the Bazaar and twinks, try Horizons out for size, just hope you got in on the ground level and power gamed to the top so you can control all the market.  EnB anybody, oops EA dumped that game, not to mention all the fun of WH h*ll and Job Terminals.  Star Wars Galaxies is not even worth mentioning as it sucked all the fun out of gaming entirely.
<br />

<br />
All these games changed from EQ, but none of it worked to create the same sort of magic feeling.  That is really a shame too.  So saying there is always another game out there that will fill your gaming needs is not always true.  Some games came close for me, but all of them always left something to be desired.</span></td>
